4 B. Any person convicted of a Class D3 criminal offense set
5 forth in this section shall be punished by imprisonment in the
6 custody of the Department of Corrections for a term of not more than
7 two (2) years and shall serve at least ten percent (10%) of the
8 sentence imposed before release from custody including release to
9 electronic monitoring pursuant to Section 510.9 of Title 57 of the
10 Oklahoma Statutes.
11 C. 1. Every person who, having been previously convicted of
12 one or two Class C or Class D criminal offenses, commits a Class D3
13 criminal offense shall, upon conviction, be punished by imprisonment
14 in the custody of the Department of Corrections for a term of not
15 less than one (1) year nor more than four (4) years and shall serve
16 at least ten percent (10%) of the sentence imposed before release
17 from custody including release to electronic monitoring pursuant to
18 Section 510.9 of Title 57 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
19 2. Every person who, having been previously convicted of three
20 Class C or Class D criminal offenses, or one or more Class Y, Class
21 A, or Class B criminal offenses, commits a Class D3 criminal offense
22 shall, upon conviction, be punished by imprisonment in the custody
23 of the Department of Corrections for a term of not less than one (1)
24 year nor more than ten (10) years and shall serve at least twenty
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3268 Page 27

1 perc ent (20%) of the sentence imposed before release from custody
2 including release to electronic monitoring pursuant to Section 510.9
3 of Title 57 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
4 D. Unless specifically exempted pursuant to subsection E of
5 this section, Section 51.1 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes this
6 title shall not apply to Class D3 criminal offenses.
7 E. The criminal offenses listed in paragraphs 69, 124, 127, and
8 177 of subsection A of this section shall be exempt from the penalty
9 provisions provided for in subsections B and C of this section.
10 Persons convicted of the criminal offenses provided for in
11 paragraphs 69, 124, 127, and 177 of subsection A of this section
12 shall be punished in accordance with the corresponding penalties
13 provided for in the Oklahoma Statutes including Section 51.1 of
14 Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title.
15 F. All Class D3 criminal offenses shall be punishable by the
16 corresponding fines as provided for in the Oklahoma Statutes.
17 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 1151, as
