9 Act, any license plate issued by any state or country other than
10 this state, unless there shall be displayed upon such vehicle at all
11 times the current license plate and decal assigned to it by Service
12 Oklahoma or the Corporation Commission or the vehicle shall display
13 evidence that the vehicle is registered as a nonresident vehicle
14 pursuant to rules promulgated by Service Oklahoma, with the
15 concurrence of the Department of Public Safety. A violation of the
16 provisions of this paragraph shall be presumed to have occurred if a
17 person who is the holder of an Oklahoma driver license operates a
18 vehicle owned by such person on the public roads or highways of this
